				<div class="comment-body"><p>Eric:</p>
<p>Every member who cast a ballot had the right under the rules to cast that ballot. Therefore, the Award Administrators could not disqualify any ballots. Doing so would be saying that the Administrators get to decide whose decisions are better than others, and this sort of activism in the Administration of the Hugo Awards is frowned upon. Unless you are saying that the Administrators should be allowed to decide what works should be allowed to actually be nominated, it&#8217;s up to the members of WSFS who have paid their membership dues to decide what works should be on the Hugo Awards ballot and what the rules for the Hugo Awards should be.</p>
</div>

