				<div class="comment-body"><p>David and Eric; Kevin is right.  You both haven&#8217;t thought this through.  You&#8217;ve slammed the Hugo administrators for not &#8220;stopping the ballot stuffing&#8221; when in fact the admins followed the rules to the letter.  Had they done otherwise they&#8217;d have been castigated for breaking those rules.  Do you imagine that anyone who paid attention this year didn&#8217;t notice that the Hugo Award nominations had been hijacked?  If so, I&#8217;m afraid that it&#8217;s you who weren&#8217;t paying attention.  Please stop blaming the Hugo Admins, and if you&#8217;re really concerned about the integrity of the Awards, then start joining the Worldcons, read the posted rules, and get involved in the process.  Fandom doesn&#8217;t need any more &#8220;armchair  quarterbacks&#8221;, we need participants.</p>
</div>

