				<div class="comment-body"><p>Ah, Greg, I see you are confusing civil discussion and angry poo flinging. In a civil discussion people do not call each other names (like Special Snowflakes) and use capitalization on words that don&#8217;t require them. Angry poo flinging is when you shout and call other people names and drag up all sorts of things that weren&#8217;t in the original disagreement.</p>
<p>When the other person just is flinging poo, the person looking for a civil discussion is rightly disgusted and insulted.</p>
</div>

